# Each of these is a symlink into the sibling checkout at ../my-<x> (its own
# independent git repo -- own remote, history, CI) -- ignored here rather
# than embedded, so this repo only tracks the workspace-level tooling that
# lives loose at the root. No trailing slash: a trailing "/" only matches a
# real directory, not a symlink-to-directory, so these leaked into `git
# status` as untracked until this was caught.
my-changelogger
my-guard
my-orchestrator
my-reporter
my-telegram-bot
my-template
my-tester
mythings-core
my-planner
my-projector
my-researcher
my-searcher
my-server
my-todo
my-uni
study
.github

.venv/
.ruff_cache/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# Local runtime ledger from ad-hoc CLI runs against the workspace root
# (e.g. myplanner/mytodo default --ledger path) -- not part of fleet-dispatch's
# own dispatch ledger (.fleet-dispatch/ledger.jsonl), which is tracked.
.mythings/

# Claude Code's local session state for this workspace -- not part of the
# fleet-dispatch tooling this repo tracks.
.claude/

# Raw per-run transcripts and pre-git backup copies -- large/verbose and
# superseded by real git history for allowed_tools.json now that this repo
# exists. The ledger keeps a pointer to each transcript's path regardless.
.fleet-dispatch/transcripts/
.fleet-dispatch/backups/

# The kill-switch marker: a local operational flag (--abort/--clear-halt),
# not fleet state worth a commit. Committing it would "halt" the fleet for
# everyone who pulls that commit and need a revert to undo.
.fleet-dispatch/HALT
